00:02:14,540 --> 00:02:17,180
(National Ice Sports Base)

44
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:18,080
Li.

45
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:19,800
Come here.

46
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:21,080
I'm busy.

47
00:02:21,890 --> 00:02:23,080
It won't take long.

48
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:24,640
Come on.

49
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:29,800
Okay.

50
00:02:34,570 --> 00:02:35,410
Tell me.

51
00:02:36,480 --> 00:02:37,320
Well,

52
00:02:37,570 --> 00:02:40,080
I've rescheduled the filming
to the rest days.

53
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:42,200
- Isn't that enough?
- Rest days

54
00:02:42,200 --> 00:02:44,130
are meant to let them rest.

55
00:02:44,130 --> 00:02:45,240
No training.

56
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,130
But you're

57
00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:47,480
making them work on rest days.

58
00:02:47,480 --> 00:02:49,170
Why don't I keep training them
all the time?

59
00:02:51,010 --> 00:02:53,130
Ice Sports are just getting viral.

60
00:02:53,290 --> 00:02:54,670
It's a great time for publicity.

61
00:02:55,200 --> 00:02:56,890
More people can know about this.

62
00:02:56,890 --> 00:02:57,730
Isn't it great?

63
00:02:57,760 --> 00:02:59,960
Only gold medals and good results

64
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:02,170
can make people truly care about this.

65
00:03:02,450 --> 00:03:04,760
It seems you're making it viral

66
00:03:04,850 --> 00:03:06,240
to attract more people,

67
00:03:06,480 --> 00:03:08,730
but if they mess up the competition,

68
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:10,080
those people will leave immediately.

69
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,890
Athletes count on good results.

70
00:03:13,360 --> 00:03:14,520
Nothing else matters.

71
00:03:16,170 --> 00:03:17,170
I get it,

72
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:19,330
but you have to be flexible, Li.

73
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:22,130
Going out is the megatrend for athletes.

74
00:03:22,730 --> 00:03:25,010
Everyone has a phone,

75
00:03:25,290 --> 00:03:26,890
and the world outside is wonderful.

76
00:03:27,410 --> 00:03:29,050
Are you going to blind their eyes?

77
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:31,290
But they're athletes.

78
00:03:31,680 --> 00:03:33,290
They accept national allowances

79
00:03:33,290 --> 00:03:35,130
and the best training.

80
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:37,290
Why should they
care about the outside world?

81
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,680
If they want to live a wonderful life
like others,

82
00:03:40,050 --> 00:03:41,730
why don't they retire?

83
00:03:43,730 --> 00:03:45,080
Why are you so stubborn?

84
00:03:48,010 --> 00:03:48,850
We can't

85
00:03:49,850 --> 00:03:51,920
reach a common ground on this.
It's enough.

86
00:03:53,330 --> 00:03:54,290
Anything else?

87
00:03:59,410 --> 00:04:00,250
No.

88
00:04:01,570 --> 00:04:02,520
I'm speechless.

89
00:04:20,970 --> 00:04:21,970
I have a filming task,

90
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,050
but I forgot where I put my tripod head.

91
00:04:24,170 --> 00:04:25,800
Do you mind being my human tripod?

92
00:04:26,680 --> 00:04:27,520
I do.

93
00:04:28,440 --> 00:04:29,280
Fine.

94
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,480
I'll have to ask Lin Ge.

95
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,320
Wait.

96
00:04:33,650 --> 00:04:34,610
Why Lin Ge?

97
00:04:35,730 --> 00:04:37,090
Xie Lingwei will be there too.

98
00:04:37,480 --> 00:04:38,320
If you don't help me,

99
00:04:38,530 --> 00:04:39,680
I'll have to ask them.

100
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:40,520
I'll help you.

101
00:04:44,560 --> 00:04:45,400
I know.

102
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:47,320
I don't want to go,

103
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,560
but our manager insisted.

104
00:04:48,770 --> 00:04:49,850
I can take two girls.

105
00:04:50,560 --> 00:04:52,360
Any advice?

106
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:54,570
Lin Ge.

107
00:05:01,410 --> 00:05:02,250
Seven Gold!

108
00:05:04,530 --> 00:05:05,370
Wei.

109
00:05:06,170 --> 00:05:07,410
I was calling you.

110
00:05:07,410 --> 00:05:08,250
What's wrong, Kai?

111
00:05:08,730 --> 00:05:10,610
Do you want to go to
a variety show with us?

112
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:12,050
Will Wei be there?

113
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:13,450
- Of course.
- Then I'm in.

114
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:14,640
I'll get changed.

115
00:05:20,880 --> 00:05:22,880
I need two more boys.

116
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,800
What variety show?

117
00:05:25,730 --> 00:05:26,770
Are you the guests?

118
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,730
What's the content?

119
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:28,810
Is there a contract?

120
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:30,530
Why are you asking so much?

121
00:05:31,120 --> 00:05:32,290
I don't want to be set up.

122
00:05:46,610 --> 00:05:48,210
Fang Chao did well today.

123
00:05:52,170 --> 00:05:53,410
Did he get a tip?

124
00:05:59,090 --> 00:06:00,170
Well done.

125
00:06:00,410 --> 00:06:02,560
How did you make it?

126
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:06,970
Yesterday, I found it hard
to lead the race,

127
00:06:07,170 --> 00:06:08,680
so I stayed close behind Seven Gold.

128
00:06:11,170 --> 00:06:12,090
That's Xinxin.

129
00:06:12,210 --> 00:06:13,480
We always call him that.

130
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:16,480
Today, I just gave it all I got

131
00:06:16,610 --> 00:06:17,530
without thinking too much.

132
00:06:18,210 --> 00:06:20,360
When Seven Gold slowed down,

133
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,200
I tried to pass him.

134
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:23,530
Anyway, I have the best stamina.

135
00:06:26,210 --> 00:06:27,050
What else?

136
00:06:27,610 --> 00:06:29,650
Just skate at my own pace

137
00:06:29,770 --> 00:06:30,850
and stay calm.

138
00:06:31,170 --> 00:06:32,850
Don't worry about being passed.

139
00:06:32,850 --> 00:06:34,290
Find a chance to pass them.

140
00:06:34,440 --> 00:06:35,440
It's okay to lead the race.

141
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:38,000
I'll convince myself

142
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,800
that I have the best stamina.

143
00:06:41,050 --> 00:06:42,850
Good. Your idea?

144
00:06:47,210 --> 00:06:48,210
He taught me that.

145
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:51,400
You?

146
00:06:53,770 --> 00:06:55,000
The last person

147
00:06:55,290 --> 00:06:56,970
has trained you to be in second place?

148
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:00,840
What happened?

149
00:07:10,170 --> 00:07:11,680
Nie Chi told me

150
00:07:12,050 --> 00:07:13,360
to tell Fang Chao,

151
00:07:14,050 --> 00:07:16,000
but he wouldn't let me tell Fang Chao

152
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:17,240
he told me to do so.

153
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,320
Is this a tongue twister?

154
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,010
No.

155
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:33,240
Why did Nie Chi come?

156
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:34,680
He gave me a flash drive,

157
00:07:34,730 --> 00:07:36,530
